missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:16:- The schema mixes descriptive and evaluative fields too early. "Exact property," "Tao verdict," and "nearest prior-art family" are descriptive; "possible proof architecture" and "first theorem-facing burden" are already strategic judgments. If the Tao verdict is not pinned down first with a worked standard, later fields will be backfilled to justify whatever survives.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:26:- The candidate examples already preload the outcome: commutator-ready scalarization, deformation constraints, stochastic circulation, vorticity-direction persistence, pressure/stress identity. Those are familiar mission motifs, not a neutral search over "exact NS structures." The chain says "for example," but examples shape selection in practice.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:29:- The expected output is too compressed for the burden. A one-sentence novelty note and a one-sentence prior-art note are not enough when several candidate families are close to known literature or to earlier internal dead ends. This is exactly how renamed prior-art overlap slips through.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:50:- The four axes are not commensurable. Tao sensitivity, endpoint closeness, prior-art distance, and narrowness of the first missing lemma measure different things and can point in opposite directions. A candidate close to an endpoint is often near prior art; a candidate far from prior art often has a very wide missing lemma. The chain offers no rule for handling these tradeoffs.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:93:The chain asks for prior-art notes, but not for explicit overlap accounting at the level of theorem mechanism. A candidate can be "not already closed" and still be functionally the same old program with renamed observables and a new Tao-sensitive gloss.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:99:- The anti-reentry rule in Step 5 is useful protection against recycled dead branches.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:104:Keep this chain only if it is treated primarily as a falsification chain. Its honest success condition is not "produce a ranked atlas with a primary branch." Its honest success condition is: determine whether any candidate survives a strict Tao-comparison protocol, survives prior-art overlap scrutiny, and exposes one typed theorem-facing burden in a way that is more than narrative attachment.
