missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/final-decider.md:10:- **Best execution fit:** the chain works directly on exact equations, localized debt, prior-art overlap, and LEI / CKN-facing insertion. That is the cleanest fit for an adversarial planning loop that needs honest kill conditions and reusable artifacts.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-01.md:71:- It underweights prior-art overlap. There is no dedicated step requiring a map from the chosen candidate to known Navier-Stokes reformulations, known commutator identities, or known pressure/localization decompositions. That omission is dangerous because this entire route lives in an area with a long history of exact-but-nonproductive repackaging.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-01.md:86:This is a serious chain, not a toy. Its strongest feature is that it tries to kill fake novelty before the program turns into notation management. Its weakness is that the anti-fake-novelty machinery is still too verbal and too path-dependent. To become reliable, it needs one tighter quantitative burden ledger, one explicit prior-art overlap audit, and less early commitment to a single endpoint and single candidate family. Until then, it is a disciplined heuristic, not yet a robust attack plan.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:15:- The menu of candidate unknowns is too broad. "Scalarized active variable," "extension variable," "projected component," and "compensated quantity" are not comparably plausible objects. Some are natural PDE unknowns; others are ad hoc packages that can always be manufactured after the fact. Without a tighter admissibility rule, Step 1 invites cherry-picking.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:51:- There is a structural mismatch between SQG-style mechanisms and NS endpoint burdens. SQG commutators help because scalar truncation and the active scalar structure align. In 3D NS, even if a commutator appears in reformulated variables, the endpoint burden usually lives in the original vector field, pressure, or vorticity geometry. The chain has not shown that the gain transfers back without restoring the full difficulty.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:61:- There is no explicit prior-art audit here. A missing lemma can look narrow only because the chain has not checked that analogous lemmas were already tried in SQG-inspired NS reformulations, projected equations, or microlocal decompositions.
