missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:62:### Step 5 - Demand a Tao-sensitive hard artifact and prior-art comparator
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:79:- The failure taxonomy is too tidy. In reality this route is likely to fail for several reasons at once: prior-art overlap, mixed-helicity collapse, reconstruction loss, and endpoint mismatch. Forcing a single label can understate how overdetermined the failure is.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:91:### 2. It is heavily exposed to prior-art redundancy
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The selected chain has a serious core idea: kill decorative reformulations early and force any surviving variable package to make contact with a theorem-facing bottleneck. That is a real strength. But the original version is still too discretionary in three places that matter: it freezes the setup too sharply and too early, it does not operationalize the burden ledger tightly enough, and it under-polices prior-art overlap and endpoint insertion debt.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:27:The original rule correctly targets cosmetic repackaging. But the critique is right that many candidates sit between trivial conjugation and genuine mechanism change. The refined chain should classify candidates at least into equivalent redistribution, ambiguous redistribution, and potentially live mechanism shift, rather than forcing an immediate binary verdict.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:80:6. Add a dedicated prior-art overlap gate before promotion.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:19:What is missing is a benchmark set. The chain should force comparison against known geometric regularity mechanisms from Constantin-Fefferman-Majda and the later vorticity-direction coherence literature. Without that, the Tao filter has no calibration.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:23:The intent is right, but the observables are not actually disjoint in any clean sense. Local Beltrami deficit, vorticity-direction regularity, and tube persistence are coupled through localization choices, amplitude thresholds, and the geometry of intense sets. If those choices are not fixed first, the "table of observables" will hide the real assumptions in normalization conventions.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:27:The bigger weakness is the way novelty is judged. The step asks whether every route from Beltrami deficit to a known criterion passes through stronger derivative control. That frames the search almost entirely as reduction to existing criteria. If a genuinely new route would proceed through a hybrid quantity not already recognized as a standard criterion, this step is set up to miss it.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:29:The kill condition is also too narrow. It attacks "Beltrami deficit alone," but many plausible geometric effects would only work in combination with concentration, anisotropy, intermittency, or localization to a coherent tube family. If the chain kills every combined route because Beltrami deficit is not sufficient by itself, that is not a mathematical obstruction; it is a modeling choice.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:35:There is also a conceptual slip in the kill condition. It says to stop if the only gain is on `u x omega` or another local/self-induced piece while the nonlocal remainder survives. But `u x omega` is not the stretching term; it belongs to the Lamb-vector side of the dynamics. Bringing it in here blurs the target mechanism. That is not a cosmetic issue. It suggests the chain has not yet fixed the exact representation of `S omega . omega` it wants to analyze.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:37:The phrase "decisive nonlocal remainder" is itself doing too much work. In some kernel representations the cancellation is distributed, and what looks like a remainder in one split is not the uniquely decisive obstruction in another. Unless the chain specifies the Biot-Savart-level formula and the localization protocol before analyzing control, Step 3 can manufacture a remainder and then declare defeat because it survives.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:49:The kill condition repeats the chain's main slogan rather than delivering a new obstruction. "If the complement of the intense-vorticity set still dominates the critical nonlocal term, terminate" is only useful if there is already a measurable criterion for domination. Otherwise it is a restatement of failure, not a diagnosis.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:65:### 2. It has weak prior-art calibration
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:67:The chain says it is meaningfully different because it centers coherent structures and geometry, but that is exactly where there is already a large literature. Without an explicit map against Constantin-Fefferman-Majda, Deng-Hou-Yu, geometric depletion work, and near-Beltrami discussions, "different" is not established. There is a real redundancy risk.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:71:"Local," "intense-vorticity region," "tube coherence," "self-induced piece," and "nonlocal remainder" all need precise localization scales and thresholds. The chain repeatedly draws hard conclusions from quantities it has not yet fixed sharply enough.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:99:- a calibrated prior-art benchmark before Step 1 can declare anything "NS-specific,"
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:41:The mission context already says the vorticity formulation also lands at the same `beta = 4/3` barrier, and that exact Beltrami cancellation evaporates under tiny perturbation. So some of the most natural Step 2 and Step 3 outputs are already strongly prefigured. The chain is at real risk of spending budget restating known negatives unless it says exactly what new localized estimate is being tested that prior work did not already rule out.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:51:- It never says which bottleneck is mission-central. Is it the De Giorgi truncated pressure contribution, a local-energy flux term, a vorticity stretching localization, or some projected interaction? Those are not interchangeable. A rewrite that helps one may do nothing for the others.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:64:- The natural test family is too familiar. Lamb-vector, projected form, and vorticity transport are exactly the rewrites one would expect to collapse back to the same structure unless some additional mechanism is injected. The mission context already suggests that at least part of this family has been effectively stress-tested.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:78:- It treats geometry, near-Beltrami structure, and tensor effects as things to subtract away before believing a gain. That is too purity-driven for this mission. The live beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism may be hybrid rather than purely algebraic.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-01.md:33:The original chain asks for prior-art notes, but not for mechanism-level overlap accounting. That is too weak. "Not already closed" is not enough if the route is functionally the same program with renamed observables. The refined chain should force explicit overlap accounting at the level of theorem mechanism, not just topic similarity.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-01.md:45:This is a serious problem. Tao sensitivity, endpoint closeness, prior-art distance, and narrowness of the first missing lemma are not naturally commensurable, and the "one primary, one secondary, one bounded negative" template biases the process toward a neat answer. The refined chain should allow zero promoted branches and should rank only within a shared architecture and gain currency.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-01.md:72:4. Add explicit mechanism-level prior-art overlap accounting.
